[size=4][u]Production Stations Tab[/u][/size]

Adds a [b]Production Stations[/b] tab to the [b]Property Owned[/b] menu in the map (the fleet/property list alongside Ships, Stations, etc.). Lists all player-owned stations that have production modules, with per-station production data and quick-navigation buttons.

[size=3][u][b]Features[/b][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]Production Stations Tab[/b]: A dedicated tab in the Property Owned menu lists all player-owned stations that contain production or processing modules.
[*] [b]Station icon with issue indicator[/b]: The station class icon is shown next to the station name and tinted in warning colour when any production module has an issue.
[*] [b]Production Overview sub-section[/b]: Expand a station row, then open the collapsible Production Overview section to see per-ware produced, consumed, and net total amounts per hour.
[*] [b]Ware icons[/b]: Each ware row shows the ware icon alongside its name for quick visual identification.
[*] [b]Production issue indicators[/b]: If any production modules for a ware are waiting for resources or waiting for storage, the ware name is highlighted in warning colour and a mouseover tooltip lists the exact issue counts per state.
[*] [b]Active module count[/b]: The module count column shows how many modules are currently running out of the total installed (e.g. [b]3/5[/b]).
[*] [b]Ware grouping[/b]: Wares are grouped into [b]Products[/b] (not consumed on-site), [b]Intermediates[/b] (produced and consumed on-site), and [b]Resources[/b] (pure inputs, not produced on-site).
[*] [b]Logical Station Overview button[/b]: Opens the Logical Station Overview for inventory and build plan details. Tinted in warning colour when the station has production issues.
[*] [b]Quick-navigation buttons[/b]: [i]Configure Station[/i] and [i]Transaction Log[/i] buttons are available on each station row.
[/list]
